The paper deals with the complexity of decision problems in Dependence Logic, which is a subfield of mathematical logic. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves model checking and satisfiability, which are central problems in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The study of parametrised complexity involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions treewidth and treedepth, which are concepts from Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of complexity classes, which is a topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG).
